# New chat = clean terminals, then localhost

**Master reference:** `C:\Projects\_tools\OWNER-PLAYBOOK.md` · `C:\Projects\_tools\SESSION-START.md`

## End of chat

When the owner says **start a new chat** or you give a **handoff block** after big work:

```powershell
powershell -File C:\Projects\_tools\stop-dev-servers.ps1 -ProjectPath C:\Projects\MacTech\website
```

Tell the owner: dev servers stopped for a clean next chat.

## Start of new chat (always)

1. **Start local dev immediately** (`npx serve . -l 3001` or `npx vercel dev`).
2. Open **http://localhost:3001** in Cursor browser — review together on screen.
3. Do not ask permission; restart if the port is stale.

See also: `local-browser-polish.mdc`.
